<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: CARLSBAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three Carlsbad High School students testified Wednesday that they purchased 
anabolic steroids from a teacher's aide during school hours. 
</P>
<P>
After a preliminary hearing, Gregory Thomas Tirona, 31, was bound over to 
Superior Court to stand trial on six charges of administering or selling 
steroids. 
</P>
<P>
The three minors all testified that they bought steroids from Tirona, also a 
part-time coach, during late October and early November of last year. All three 
said they paid $25 a bottle for the illegal substance, which they said they 
purchased during school hours in front of Tirona's classroom. 
</P>
<P>
In deciding that Tirona should face trial, San Diego Municipal Judge Fredric 
Link said the evidence presented offered "more than a strong suspicion" that 
Tirona sold the illegal drug to minors. 
</P>
<P>
An arraignment and trial setting was scheduled for July 26. 
</P>
<P>
Tirona, a Carlsbad resident, remains free on his own recognizance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
