<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 CONVICTED OF MURDERING SYLMAR MAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After a week of deliberations, a San Fernando Superior Court jury Wednesday 
convicted two men of murdering a Sylmar man who was chaperoning a Sweet 16 
party last year. 
</P>
<P>
John Tanner, 23, of Lake View Terrace was found guilty of shooting John Shaw, 
23. Jeffrey Evans, 24, of Lake View Terrace was found guilty of second-degree 
murder for aiding and abetting Tanner. 
</P>
<P>
But the jurors were still deliberating the charges against Dennis Elliot, 24, 
of Pacoima, who prosecutors charge was involved in the quarrel that provoked 
the shooting. 
</P>
<P>
During the eight-week trial, Deputy Dist. Atty. Edward Nison argued that 
Tanner, Evans and Elliot, who he said are gang members, approached Shaw as he 
stood with other guests in front of the house in the 14900 block of Aztec 
Street in Sylmar. Evans asked the party-goers if they were affiliated with 
gangs. Shaw replied that he was not, which Tanner interpreted as a slight, 
Nison said. 
</P>
<P>
Tanner shot Shaw four or five times in the back and chest, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Tanner testified he was asleep at home after drinking with friends all day when 
the shooting took place. 
</P>
<P>
Evans and Elliot also are charged with attempted murder in a drive-by shooting 
involving a 20-year-old Pacoima man, Cedric Finley, in Lake View Terrace about 
half an hour before the Sylmar killing. Finley was shot at four times but was 
uninjured, Nison said. 
</P>
<P>
The jury was still deliberating charges stemming from that shooting. 
</P>
<P>
Sentencing for Tanner and Evans was set for Aug. 11. Both face a maximum 
sentence of life imprisonment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
