<HEADLINE>
<P>
AMERICAN LEGION BASEBALL; 
</P>
<P>
PANORAMA CITY WINS EASTERN DIVISION TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Joe Cascione singled to score Dave Garcia in the bottom of the eighth inning 
Wednesday at Poly High as Panorama City rallied to defeat Sun Valley, 6-5, and 
clinch the District 20 Eastern Division title. 
</P>
<P>
Panorama City (16-4), which trailed, 4-0, after 4 1/2 innings, rallied for two 
runs in the fifth inning and three runs in the sixth to forge a 5-5 tie. 
</P>
<P>
In the eighth, Roland De La Maza hit a leadoff double and Garcia was walked 
intentionally. Shane Wight followed with a single, but De La Maza was thrown 
out trying to score. 
</P>
<P>
Cascione followed with a hit to score Garcia from third. 
</P>
<P>
De La Maza (6-0) pitched three innings in relief to earn the win. 
</P>
<P>
In other District 20 games: 
</P>
<P>
Woodland Hills West 8, West Hills 4 -- Woodland Hills West scored four runs 
with two out in the third inning to erase a 2-1 deficit and roll to a Western 
Division win at Chaminade High. 
</P>
<P>
Jason Cohen and Jeff Marks each singled to score a run and West added two 
unearned runs off West Hills left-hander Ted Corcoran. 
</P>
<P>
Woodland Hills West (19-3), which already had clinched the division title, 
added three runs in the fourth. Bobby Kim belted a two-run double and Ricky 
Banuelos scored on a ground out by Del Marine. 
</P>
<P>
Left-hander Lance Gibson (6-1) pitched four innings, striking out seven, to 
improve his career record to 19-3. 
</P>
<P>
Woodland Hills East 6, Foothill Valley 0 -- Chris Brown pitched a four-hitter 
and struck out seven for Woodland Hills East in the inter-division game at 
Taft. 
</P>
<P>
Brown (6-1) allowed one hit in the first five innings. 
</P>
<P>
After taking a 1-0 lead in the first, Woodland Hills East (12-7) scored three 
runs in the fourth. 
</P>
<P>
Jamie Ziecheck led off the inning with his first home run. And after two walks 
and an out, Rich Shapiro and Alan Puana hit consecutive run-scoring singles. 
</P>
<P>
Van Nuys-Notre Dame 12, North Hollywood 4 -- Lou Tapia was three for four, 
including a three-run home run, and Kevin Milligan was three for four with 
three RBIs as Van Nuys-Notre Dame (9-10) pounded right-hander Mark Williams for 
14 hits in an Eastern Division game at Notre Dame High. 
</P>
<P>
Right-hander Bill Jay (3-2) scattered nine hits and struck out six while going 
the distance. 
</P>
<P>
Newhall-Saugus 7, Reseda 0 -- Right-handers Glenn Terry and Ben Ealy combined 
on a four-hitter and Terry blasted a two-run home run to lead Newhall-Saugus in 
an inter-division game at Reseda High. 
</P>
<P>
Terry (3-1) struck out three batters in four innings to earn the win. Ealy was 
two for four. 
</P>
<P>
Westlake-Agoura 8, Santa Monica 8 -- Westlake-Agoura scored three runs in the 
last two innings to forge a tie in the District 16 inter-division game at 
Westlake High. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Suarez, who scored the tying run on a balk, had three doubles in five 
at-bats. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Early retirement -- A shrouded Ben Ealy of Newhall-Saugus cannot hide 
from Louis Vanacore, who tags him out at third base. Ealy and his mates rose to 
dust off Reseda, 7-0. RICARDO DeARATANHA / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
