Mead Corp.: The Dayton, Ohio, paper products firm said second-quarter profit 
dipped 15% to $62.2 million from a year ago. Revenue rose to a record $1.21 
billion, up 4%. Although earnings from operations climbed 10.6% in the period, 
the firm said net income eased because of its restructuring program. 
</P>
