<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CBS Inc.: The New York-based broadcast company said second-quarter profit fell 
8% to $118.8 million because of higher prime-time programming costs. Revenue, 
however, rose 4% to $772 million. CBS cited an extraordinary loss of $200,000 
in the first half of 1989 to pay down debt. 
</P>
<P>
Tables, Page 8 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Corporate Earnings 
</P>
