<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MUSIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A company featuring American operatic artists has arrived in Beijing to present 
the first prominent American cultural event there since the military crackdown 
on pro-democracy demonstrators last month. Although there is a U.S. travel 
advisory in effect for China, Joann Grillo, managing director of Ambassadors of 
Opera and Concert Worldwide, said, "No one in our government told us not to 
come. In fact, every American embassy and official along the way has encouraged 
us as a step toward friendship and peace." The Ambassadors of Opera and Concert 
Worldwide, an independent company, has staged operas and musicals throughout 
the world since 1983. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
