<HEADLINE>
<P>
YOUTH THEATER CLASS TO PRESENT 'GREASE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PICO RIVERA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This summer's Theater in the Park, a countywide musical theater workshop for 
teen-agers, will present "Grease," a musical story about young love in the 
1950s that gained fame as a feature film starring John Travolta and Olivia 
Newton John. 
</P>
<P>
The theater workshop, made up local high school students, is a two-month summer 
conservatory at Smith Park. Students pay $100 to enroll in the workshop and 
attend all-day classes Monday through Friday in preparation for performances 
Aug. 25 and 26 and Sept. 1 and 2. 
</P>
<P>
Professional actors are taking students through all phases of musical theater 
production, including movement, dance, acting, voice, scene painting and 
costume construction techniques. 
</P>
