<TEXT>
<P>
A new study suggests that eating large amounts of dairy products, especially 
yogurt and cottage cheese, may increase the risk of developing ovarian cancer, 
a researcher said. A team of researchers affiliated with Harvard Medical School 
found for the first time that women with ovarian cancer were more likely to eat 
dairy products, especially yogurt and cottage cheese, compared to healthy 
women. Dr. Daniel Cramer, who headed the study published in the British journal 
The Lancet, stressed the findings need to be confirmed before recommending 
women eat less dairy products. Scientists believe that a sugar found in milk, 
cheese, yogurt and other dairy products known as galactose may damage the 
ovaries. 
