<P>
YOUNG JOURNALIST HONORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Joy Shioshita, a recent graduate of Venice High School, has been awarded the 
annual Clive Hoffman Media Scholarship for her outstanding school achievement 
and potential in the field of journalism. 
</P>
<P>
An aspiring print journalist, Shioshita plans to attend the UC Berkeley this 
fall and major in English or sociology. 
</P>
<P>
Shioshita was editor in chief of the Venice High School newspaper and of L.A. 
Youth, a citywide newspaper written and edited by teen-age journalists. She 
also was bureau chief and reporter for the affiliated Youth News Service, based 
in Washington. 
</P>
<P>
The four-year, $5,000 scholarship is provided by Clive and Carol Hoffman and 
co-sponsored by the Greater Los Angeles Press Club. 
</P>
