<P>
CONSERVANCY FUNDS VETOED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gov. George Deukmejian vetoed from the state's 1989-90 budget a $3-million 
appropriation for the Santa Monica Mountains Conservancy to acquire land near 
Malibu Creek State Park and in the Santa Susana Mountains. In his veto message 
last week, Deukmejian said there were insufficient funds from a 1984 parkland 
bond act to make the purchases. 
