<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
McCaw-Lin Talks Under Way: McCaw Cellular Communications said discussions are 
continuing on the possible acquisition of Lin Broadcasting at a price higher 
than its current bid of $110 a share. The Kirkland, Wash.-based cellular 
telephone company, which originally bid $120 a share for Lin before a court 
killed Lin's efforts to acquire certain valuable cellular interests, said it 
has discussed other matters with New York-based Lin. Talks included the 
possibility of acquiring certain Lin cellular interests or acquiring Lin at a 
reduced price after the proposed spinoff of Lin's seven broadcast stations, 
McCaw said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
