<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
PARENTS HOPE TO SAVE SCHOOL'S MUSIC PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A group of parents of Fountain Valley High School students have announced plans 
to raise $43,000 by August to keep the school's music program intact. 
</P>
<P>
Because of declining enrollment, the financially struggling Huntington Beach 
Union High School District has had to cut back varied programs, including the 
Fountain Valley High School's music program. 
</P>
<P>
Parents have formed the Vocal Music Parents Assn./Vocal Music Foundation and 
plan to raise enough money to pay salary and benefits for a full-time music 
teacher for the school. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, contact the foundation at 17816 Bushard St., Fountain 
Valley, Calif. 92708, or call the school at (714) 962-3301. 
</P>
</TEXT>
