<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: FULLERTON MAN MISSING FROM 
LOW-SECURITY JAIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 26-year-old Fullerton man was missing from the Theo Lacy minimum-security 
jail facility during an early morning bed check, a Sheriff's Department 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Manuel S. Orosco, 26, was absent after a bed check revealed only his jail 
clothing, Sheriff's Sgt. Richard Paddock said. 
</P>
<P>
Orosco, who was awaiting trial on a drug charge, is not considered dangerous, 
he said. 
</P>
<P>
An investigation is being conducted to determine how Orosco escaped, Paddock 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
