<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: MEDICAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Leslie Berkman, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
St. Joseph Hospital will open its Irvine Health Center on Saturday. The center 
is an outreach facility that will provide a broad array of diagnostic and 
treatment services. 
</P>
<P>
Dennis Gaschen, a spokesman for the Orange-based hospital, said the 
40,000-square-foot building at 4050 Barranca Parkway will contain the offices 
of two primary care physician groups, Doctors of Children for Orange County and 
Doctors of Women Health Center. 
</P>
<P>
He said there are also plans to add internal medicine and family practice 
groups. Besides primary physicians, he said, the center will provide time-share 
offices for at least 40 specialists. 
</P>
<P>
Gaschen said the opening of the Irvine facility is "part of a growing trend for 
the hospital to establish primary care networks throughout Orange County." St. 
Joseph has also said it will open an urgent care center in east Orange this 
fall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
