It was erroneously reported in James Flanigan's column Wednesday that 
Integrated Resources entered Chapter 11 bankruptcy proceedings last month. 
Although the firm halted payments on $864 million of loans and commercial paper 
on June 16, it continues to operate and is restructuring its debt with the 
cooperation of creditors. 
