<P>
BUSH'S RAINSTORM GESTURE OF CHIVALRY COSTS AGENT A COAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PARIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Remember the raincoat that President Bush so generously took off and gave to an 
elderly woman in a rainstorm in Budapest, Hungary? Well, it wasn't his. 
</P>
<P>
Barbara Bush said today that the raincoat belonged to a Secret Service agent 
who was accompanying the President to an arrival ceremony in a downtown square 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
After making an abbreviated speech, Bush spotted the woman in the crowd, 
drenched to the bone after a heavy downpour. He took off the raincoat and gave 
it to her -- a seemingly selfless gesture that attracted a lot of publicity. 
</P>
<P>
Promising to replace the agent's coat, Barbara Bush said she and the President 
know the exact brand they have to get. 
</P>
