<TEXT>
<P>
Autoclave Engineers Inc. said today it has withdrawn its tender offer for 
Torrance-based Tylan Corp. after the Federal Trade Commission's decision to 
block the acquisition on antitrust grounds. 
</P>
<P>
"The process of proving our case in court . . . would be time-consuming and 
disruptive to our employees and would create uncertainty for our customers and 
suppliers," said Thomas Guelch, Autoclave's chief financial officer. 
