<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
W. GERMANS BEAT U.S. IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BERLIN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
West Germany edged the United States 7-6 today in third-day action of the FINA 
World Cup water polo tournament. Italy trimmed Hungary 7-6 in another match of 
the tournament, which features the world's eight top-ranked water polo teams. 
</P>
<P>
Dirk Theismann and Hagen Stamm collected two goals each for West Germany, and 
Julian Harvey had two for the United States. 
</P>
<P>
After shutting out the Americans in the first two periods, West Germany led 4-1 
entering the final quarter. The Americans stormed back to tie the game but 
still fell short despite outscoring the West Germans 5-3 in the last quarter. 
</P>
